+## Add a space-backed organ
+
+A module that brings a new AtomSpace should declare syntax and runtime
+separately:
+
+1. Add `(SignatureSpace name)` and any `(SkillSignature ...)` atoms beside the module.
+2. Bind the actual MeTTa space in the module entry file.
+3. Call `(register-space "name" &name role)` so `space-known`, `space-handle`, `space-pressure`, and `space-transform` can reason over it.
+4. Add `(register-space-alias name "name")` if older symbol-form calls should work too.
+5. If the space is durable runtime memory, call `(register-space-persistence "name" ./repos/OmegaClaw-Core/memory/name.metta runtime-state)` and load/save it with `(load-runtime-space "name")` / `(save-runtime-space "name")` during the organ's lifecycle.
+
+This keeps plug-in spaces inspectable in MeTTa instead of extending Python or
+adding more nested conditionals.
